commitResults.messageTitle: Save tasks and load data from hard disk
commitResults.messageBody:
The code now allows:
* saving of tasks in hard disk automatically
* loading of data from hard disk when chatbot starts up

commitResults.messageTitle: Teach the chatbot to understand dates and times
commitResults.messageBody:
The code will allow the chatbot to understand:

* store deadline dates and times as a java.time.LocalDateTime in the task object
* store start and end of event dates and times as java.time.LocalDateTime in the task object

The code has been refactored to extract out closely related code as

classes which includes:

* Abstract class: Command
* Classes extending Command class: AddDeadlineCommand, AddEventCommand,

AddTodoCommand, DeleteCommand, ExitCommand, ListCommand,

MarkAsDoneCommand, MarkAsUndoneCommand

* Classes: Ui, Storage, Parser, TaskList, Duke

commitResults.messageTitle: Organise the classes into suitable java packages
commitResults.messageBody:
The code has been organised into suitable java packages as followed:

* An overall duke package
* Packages in duke: command, exception, storage, task, ui

commitResults.messageTitle: Add JUnit tests to test behaviour of the code
commitResults.messageBody:
The code has two added test classes:

* TaskListTest class -- tests for addTask, deleteTask, get,
getting and deleting invalid task

* ToDoTest class -- tests for toString, markAsDone, markAsNotDone,

createTaskFromFormattedString

commitResults.messageTitle: Package the App as a JAR file
commitResults.messageBody:
Edited on the build.gradle file to successfully package the app
to an executable JAR file.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add JavaDoc comments to the code
commitResults.messageBody:
Added header comments to all non-private classes/methods,
and non-trivial private methods.

commitResults.messageTitle: Tweak the code to comply with the coding standard
commitResults.messageBody: The code now complies with the given coding standard.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add JavaDoc comments to the code
commitResults.messageBody: Added additional header comments to all class-level members.
